<a name="1225"></a><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#efefef"><td width=500><p><b>Re: High End Game = End Game</b> <font size=2>(Score: 1)<br>by Ghwomb on Saturday, March 17 @ 20:54:18 EST<br>(<a href="user.php?op=userinfo&uname=Ghwomb">User Info</a>) </font></td></tr><tr><td>Heh, I forsee a mass exodos coming... personally I think Dark Age of Camelot is in my future =P</td></tr></table><br><p>[ No Comments Allowed for Anonymous, please <a href="user.php">register</a>  ]</font><p></ul></p><a name="1233"></a><table width=99% border=0><tr bgcolor="#efefef"><td width=500><p><b>Re: High End Game = End Game</b> <font size=2>(Score: 0)<br>by Anonymous on Sunday, March 18 @ 06:43:49 EST</font></td></tr><tr><td>This is the normal life circle of these types of games...<br>
<br>
I bet many of you still remember back in the days where you as a totally naked n00b ran around just looking at the sun set or being scared out of your pants when entering Blackburrow...<br>
<br>
When the first admiration is done you suddenly feel like there is nothing more to admire and next step is either: <br>
<br>
1) Get the highest level possible<br>
2) Get as much phat lewtz as possible<br>
3) Get as many high level chars as possible<br>
4) Try to roleplay as much as possible<br>
5) All of the above - though 4 dont really go much together with 1-3 if you are a real roleplayer.<br>
<br>
Now, you state that you like the game before when it was just Everquest and not now when its some foo's "balancing issues"... Well, that foo is just not only Verant but YOU (and here I mean you as players in general) that wished for it... Cause remember when you were a little wizard or whatever class and you couldnt kill anything by yourself... But that was aaallllll just fine for you to begin with... Cause you were to busy being frighten of those gnolls in Blackburrow to care... You were having so much fun grouping with others to hunt down those gnolls you never cared that you couldnt solo shit...<br>
<br>
But then you suddenly started to ENVY others as you saw the neighbours lawn was much greener than yours... Yes... You suddenly saw a druid kite around with some bandit in West Karana and killing him SOLO without any trouble... And he was lower level than YOU... And you couldnt even dream of trying to charge a bandit on your own!!!<br>
<br>
And what is that, you say... A necromancer with some sort or skeleton assistant that is wiping out the whole mino cave in steamfont alone ! WTF is up with that... You can barely nuke for 78 damage and only 5 times and you would be out of mana... Phew... That is outragious... What is up with this game YOU start to say and start /whining that necromancers, druids and mages are way to powerful and should be balanced etc etc...<br>
<br>
